Author: kuerax
Content:
We're proud to announce that D5 will create a blockchain data marketplace on Ocean, using our create-react-app, to benefit our community of early adopters & blockchain enthusiasts. D5 is a member of the Ocean Shipyard Program to accelerate projects to the next level.

Data Scientist and D5 Co-founder Alex Svanevik: "We're excited to make blockchain data more accessible w/ Ocean. We are thrilled to contribute to this future becoming a reality"

D5 is an organization of data scientists and data engineers that provide knowledge and expertise to start-ups and corporation in creating and executing their data and AI strategies.

â€œThe Filecoin dev grants program allows teams like Protofire to build valuable Web3 integrations. Weâ€™re thrilled theyâ€™ve undertaken this integration to enable users to seamlessly store their data on a decentralized network.â€ Jonathan Victor, Filecoin
â€œWe believe in the power of data, decentralized data markets, & open-source tech. Filecoin was an obvious solution to better suit usersâ€™ needs in dataset size, redundancy, speed of retrieval, & cost" Manuel Garcia ProtoFire

Author: kuerax
Content:
Ocean Protocol and Energy Web will collaborate to unlock IoT energy data, boosting distributed energy resource (DER) optimization and enabling private data monetization.

The bridge b/t Ocean & Energy Web will enable customers, vendors, & grid operators to send power telemetry data from DERs to Ocean. Oceanâ€™s algorithms will run analytics to uncover patterns that can inform better renewable energy grid integration and IoT device optimization.

â€œWe aim to set a benchmark on how energy domains can securely share & monetize their private data. Weâ€™re leveraging Ocean v3 Datatokens to tokenize data from EW devices, creating an opportunity for these tokens to be used as instruments in DeFi projectsâ€ Razvan Olteanu, Ocean COO

â€œA bridge from DERs enabled with EW-DOS to Oceanâ€™s marketplaces can help the energy sector â€˜crack the codeâ€™ while retaining data privacy when and where it is neededâ€ Micha Roon, Energy Web CTO

https://oceanprotocol.com/press/2020-09-15-ocean-energy-web-collaboration-announcement

Author: kuerax
Content:
We're excited to announce the launch of Ocean Shipyard, an early-stage program for Web3 focused startups & projects to add value to the Data Economy while using Ocean technology. Ocean Protocol Foundation has allocated 20M $OCEAN to fund these projects.

Ocean Shipyard advances projects by providing direct support to teams. In addition to our in-house expertise in blockchain, AI, and data, we advise Shipyard participants in building with Ocean tech, the art of community building, and running bizdev.

â€œThere are many great minds & ideas in Web3. We want to harness the innovative thinking that exists within and beyond our community to advance the Data Economy. Ocean Shipyard is a launchpad for the next big thing in blockchain and data.â€ Sheridan Johns, Ocean's Head of Ecosystem.

We're looking for startups & entrepreneurs who are creating opensource software, with a real world use case, that will benefit the broader Ocean ecosystem. Apply today to take your project to the next level!

https://blog.oceanprotocol.com/announcing-the-ocean-shipyard-program-612f9256b5b7

Author: Daniel from Ocean#3725
Content:
PARTNERSHIP | We're teaming up with Raven Protocol to add Federated Learning to Ocean Market via Compute-to-Data. Raven's decentralized algorithms allow cost-efficient training of neural networks.

https://blog.oceanprotocol.com/ocean-protocol-and-raven-protocol-to-add-federated-learning-to-ocean-market-via-compute-to-data-f0314575d3c8

Raven's mission is to provide efficient & faster training of deep neural networks by developing a distributed network of compute nodes for AI and ML. Using Raven, compute jobs on Ocean Market can be run in a decentralized fashion. Algorithms are initialized in a Kubernetes cluster (on e.g. AWS or Azure) responsible for running the actual compute jobs, out of sight of marketplace clients & end users. 

Read the blog post for details, and for thoughts from Razvan Olteanu, COO at Ocean Protocol, and Kailash Ahirwar, Co-Founder at Raven Protocol & author of "Generative Adversarial Networks Projects: Build next-generation generative models using TensorFlow and Keras."

Author: dotunwilfred.eth
Content:
@OceanDAO_ Updates:

(1) OceanDAO Stewards are being introduced
(2) Quadratic Voting will not be deployed for Round 11 

Join the OceanDAO Governance Evolution Call today @ 4PM GMT and share your ideas on how to further grow the program: https://t.co/OewXheNYLP https://t.co/yFc0sBNcH9

(1) Nurturing the growing community of our monthly grants program is a core pillar. Thus, as of Round 11 we are introducing OceanDAO Stewards, who will meet with grantees before the proposal deadline, to provide guidance towards ROI > 1. Stewards will also be in charge with vetting teams to be eligible for higher-level rewards. A >50% vote by all stewards in multisig is needed to access the higher funds.

(2) Quadratic Voting remains a key deliverable for @OceanDAO_, however we will continue working and improving it, to avoid the following:
 
- Sybil attack
- An orchestrated attack
- Become a central authority in grant-voting outcomes
- Fracture voter & grantee participation
<https://twitter.com/oceanprotocol/status/145299403364>

Let's take a dive into what they aim to accomplish ğŸ‘‡

VORN envisions integrating the Ocean wallet into their app and enable the trading of VORN member bio-metric and spatial data on the Ocean marketplace while also utilizing Ocean's compute-to-data offering for third party research.

Problems to solve: 

ğŸš© Promoting user-exclusive data control rights 
ğŸš© Lack of marketplaces where data has value and can be securely exchanged

âœ… Bio-metric data measurement
âœ… Data cleaning and analysis
âœ… Data set collection for professional and semi-professional athletes

Access details here: https://t.co/XarUBFaelQ

As the name suggests, Disrupt MLS aims to disrupt the centralization of homebuyer inventory data on the MLS. The project will seek to gain traction in markets where there is no centralized MLS.

Problems to solve:

ğŸš© Cut out the realtors, traditional MLS, and associated fees to enable unrestricted access to data

Author: birususama
Content:
"Ocean Protocol Foundation is proud to support innovative projects at the forefront of building the open data economy and Ocean Shipyard is designed to help these projects succeed."

Sheridan Johns/@sjohns, Enterprise Lead at Ocean Protocol

Ocean Shipyard is a complementary funding layer to @OceanDAO_, which is a bottom-up, community-curated grants program. Ocean Shipyard has a top-down approach - the OPF selects the proposals and requires delivery according to specific milestones.
Grant payments are contingent on the successful delivery of project milestones within a stipulated time frame and will be made in OCEAN tokens.
Launched in 2020, the 1st edition of Shipyard received  60+ applications from projects keen to build on Ocean Protocol. Previous Shipyard grant recipients include @DataunionA, @swashapp, @TransportGenie & many more, each team exploring different approaches to data monetization.

More details on the grants program are available here:
https://oceanprotocol.com/press/2022-02-17-ocean-protocol-shipyard-launch

âœ… Low - 2,000 USD

Data Farming. Ocean ecosystem. What are H2O plans to remove OCEAN tokenâ€™s volatility from transactions?

The latest blogpost by @H2O_data dives into how data as an asset class is going to be effectively monetized with Data Farming! âš’ï¸

Let's unlock ğŸ”

âœ… Yield farming has been a driving narrative in DeFi and is a method that allows crypto users to earn more cryptocurrency and provides protocols with added liquidity to fuel protocol growth.

âœ… Unlike yield farming, Ocean's Data Farming has actual utility for all stakeholders. The liquidity providers earn additional tokens, the protocol receives sustainable liquidity, and the users can trust the protocol's secured data assets.

âœ… The Ocean Data Farmers are responsible for sourcing liquidity to the OCEAN datatoken pools; and, in turn,  receive rewards in the form of OCEAN tokens. The data farmers can further multiply these rewards by using their stake datasets.

âœ… Transacting with Ocean Protocol's datasets requires using the OCEAN token and the H2O stable asset acts as a medium of exchange and unit of account and can be used for transacting with datatokens in the Ocean protocol - without token volatility.

Content:
OceanONDA V4 is now live! ğŸŒŠğŸ¥³

ğŸŒŠOcean Protocol is proud to launch its 4th upgrade. This is a massive release, so thank you to the core team and the Ocean ecosystem for contributing to this major milestone for the Web3 space and the New Data Economy.  

ğŸŒŠOcean Protocol is proud to launch its 4th upgrade. This is a massive release, so thank you to the core team and the Ocean ecosystem for contributing to this major milestone for the Web3 space and the New Data Economy.  
#theyearofadoption

OceanONDA V4 solves rug pulls in the datatoken pools, introduces data NFTs, expands the options for the community to monetize, and delivers updates to Ocean Market. 

ğŸ’¡Read more about the new features and the 18 month-journey to get here:
https://blog.oceanprotocol.com/oceanonda-v4-production-has-arrived-cb4fe8faaf39

All the key components of OceanONDA V4 are deployed to production chains on Ethereum mainnet and Polygon, Binance Smart Chain, Energy Web, and Moonriver.

1/ It is safer to stake liquidity in datatoken pools by solving rug pulls, through one-sided staking.âœ…

2/ A centrepiece of the OceanONDA V4 release is the introduction of ERC721 data NFTs. A data NFT represents the copyright (or exclusive license against copyright) for a data asset on the blockchain â€” the â€œbase IPâ€ (intellectual property).âœ…

3/ OceanONDA V4 has improved community monetization for selling data, running a marketplace or providing liquidity and it added a fourth one - by running your own Provider. This means more revenue upside and more flexibility in how fees can be charged.âœ…

ğŸ’¡Ocean Market V4 is live in production with updates like a new publish flow and a data NFT image generator:

https://market.oceanprotocol.com

Author: dotunwilfred.eth
Content:
ğŸŒŠOcean Market is a decentralised data marketplace that allows data publishers to monetise their data assets in a privacy-preserving way. 

Data Providers: Publishing a dataset takes no more than 3 minutes. 

Just follow these simple steps ğŸ‘‡

1. Head over to the publish form here: https://market.oceanprotocol.com/publish/1 and enter the metadata ğŸ“ of your Ocean Data NFT  

Note: You can publish your Data NFT on different chains. Namely #Ethereum #polygon #BSC #EWC #MoonRiver ğŸ’¥

2. Select the #data access type âš’

"Download" is for non-sensitive information. It allows data buyers to download your dataset

"Compute-to-Data" is for sharing sensitive data. Data is not downloadable, and the buyer can run compute jobs on it without accessing confidential data

3. Set the price ğŸ’° 

"Fixed" prices the datatoken at the entered amount of OCEAN

"Dynamic" creates an automated market for your dataset. This means the price is determined by the ratio of OCEAN to datatoken

"Free" gives the datatoken for free via creating a faucet

4. Review & Publish âœ… 

This will create the tokens & pricing, construct & encrypt DDO via Ocean providers, and eventually publish the encrypted DDO on-chain as part of the Data NFT

<https://twitter.com/oceanprotocol/status/1542858813073772545?s=20&t=Aa6KaYfR8XFjihZMc5l4nQ>

Author: dotunwilfred.eth
Content:
Important âš ï¸

At the end of last week, we noticed suspicious behaviour in several Ocean Market data pools that resulted in a loss of some OCEAN.

Here is an overview of what happened since, why it happened and the mitigation measures that are being taken to prevent further attack vectors.

Let's unpackğŸ‘‡ 

https://t.co/qqIv32svbe

ğŸš¨ The first series of attacks took place last Thu around 7pm CEST time. Attacker executed the following actions in loop:

Stake OCEAN in a data pool
Buy datatokens
Unstake OCEAN
Sell datatokens

Through this sequence, small amounts of OCEAN were drained from data pools.

After reports from the Ocean community, we implemented the following change as short-term mitigation:

âœ…Raised the swap fee to 15% to make the attacks unprofitable

âœ…We also explored solutions in how to mitigate the risks long term

ğŸš¨ On Monday, July 11, the attacker re-started their attempts to drain Ocean data pools, this time using over $600,000 OCEAN.

https://twitter.com/oceanprotocol/status/1546849549259767808>
@everyone

Author: dotunwilfred.eth
Content:
#veOCEAN is coming to the Ocean ecosystem ğŸŒŠ 

Following feedback from the community and recent learnings, we are introducing veOCEAN to best align the incentives of token holders and liquidity providers.  

Continue reading ğŸ‘‡ <https://t.co/Cme16cby0x>

How?ğŸŒŸ 

veOCEAN holders can lock their $OCEAN tokens over a time period to earn rewards and voting power. The longer the lock period, the higher the rewards and the voting power.

They can also vote on proposals and earn rewards, both from consume fees and data farming.

veOCEAN holders can earn passive rewards, solely by locking their $OCEAN. 

Or, they can be active by allocating veOCEAN to higher-quality datasets for greater earnings.

Going forward, veOCEAN will be the main mechanism for staking $OCEAN and for curation of datasets. Itâ€™s lower risk than Ocean datatoken pools, and it delivers similar benefits.

When? â°

Content:
ğŸ‰ğŸŒŠAcentrik, a decentralized data marketplace by Mercedes-Benz built on Ocean Protocolâ€Š, is now in Enterprise Release! 

Acentrikâ€™s collaboration with Ocean Protocol began in 2020, with a proof of concept exploring decentralized data orchestration for Mercedes-Benz. The pilot project was successful and this led to further collaboration and development of Acentrik Version 1.0. As part of the collaboration with Ocean Protocol, Acentrik Version 1.0 has leveraged and integrated specific Ocean features, with key adaptations made for enterprise users.

Acentrik is a fork of Ocean Market and makes use of the OceanONDA V4 smart contracts and libraries. Built on the foundation of Ocean technology, Acentrikâ€™s mission is to make it easier for enterprises to unlock the value of decentralized data and enable data sharing with the principle of data sovereignty at the core. With Acentrikâ€™s V1.0, enterprises can now publish datasets with parameters.
For a comprehensive overview, read the dedicated blog post here: <https://lnkd.in/d7HgN83S>

Content:

DesightsAI launches today! ğŸ‰ 

Who is DesightsAI?

DesightsAI is a Web3 data competition platform built on Ocean Protocol tech for the toughest #AI & #ML challenges. They launched today in closed Alpha, kicking off the 3rd round of Ocean Protocol's Predict-ETH data challenge.

/2

How does DesightsAI relate to Ocean Protocol?

DesightsAI is an initiative bootstrapped by the community, and built on Ocean Protocol technology to achieve their mission of monetizing competition entries. Ocean Protocol funded DesightsAI's latest Predict-ETH data challenge.

/3

What does DesightsAI do?

Organizations and DAOs can fund challenges on the DesightsAI platform and invite brightest minds in the Data and AI industry to solve these challenges.

Desights creates a royalty structure for competition submissions using Ocean Protocol tech by tokenizing each submission with an Ocean dataNFT!

Author: birususama
Content:
There's value in the data we generate just for being alive: our conversations, our pictures, our genetic information...

AI tools like ChatGPT are ALREADY trained on data that you produced and posted online for free.

What if you could force AI to *pay you for your data*? ğŸ§

Enter, Ocean Protocol.

When you use Ocean Protocol to tokenize your data on the blockchain, it becomes part of that immutable ledger of transactions that records ownership of the data token and you can use Ocean's smart contracts to transfer that token (for money or for free).

Flip the script on AI.

Upload data that you know AI tools will find valuable to the Ocean Market. 

Make AI pay you back.

Author: doteth
Content:
@everyone

ğŸŒŠ Oceaners, weâ€™re writing this message as a result of the unfortunate incident that happened on our Discord server recently. This morning we noticed that someone managed to gain control of the server by exploiting a vulnerability in the captcha system. As a result, they created a fake airdrop, and although our team was fast in catching this, it's possible that some of you may have accessed the link and experienced losses.

First, we want to say that we are sorry for any inconvenience and potential loss that this incident may have caused you. We understand it might have raised some concern and frustration within our community. And we take this very seriously, actively discussing internally, to find how we can best support those affected.

We want to assure you that our core team members are always taking numerous security measures, including two-factor authentication (2FA) and strong passwords for the accounts. Unfortunately, determined hackers can still find ways to exploit vulnerabilities, even with such precautions in place.

We want to emphasize that no OCEAN tokens were drained during this incident, and there were no casualties apart from the potential loss resulting from accessing the fraudulent link. However, we understand the impact this event can have on individuals within our community, and we are committed to learning from this experience to improve the security and resilience of our platform moving forward.
Moving forward, if you have been affected by this incident, please fill in this form: https://forms.gle/FbcG8gRVugZyq59s7.

We genuinely care about our community and will do everything we can to provide the necessary support and guidance during this time.

In light of recent events, we kindly remind our valued community members to exercise caution and diligence when it comes to airdrops or clicking on links. Take extra precautions, verify the authenticity of sources, and ensure official authorization. Your safety is paramount. If you're uncertain about any activity or encounter, please reach out to us. Together, we'll continue fostering a secure and resilient ecosystem. Your trust and support mean the world to us, and we're putting in our effort to prevent any similar incidents from happening in the future.

Thank you all for your understanding and being part of our incredible community and remember to stay vigilant! ğŸ™Œ
